# Workflow Run Prompt Apply Verify

{% include "runtime/partial/stage_verification_contract.md.j2" %}

## Verification Workflow

For workflow_run_prompt_apply, verify that source-scope instructions from workflow_run_prompt are represented in source_type_allow_list when they clearly limit allowed source types. An unrestricted request for all source types must be represented by an empty source_type_allow_list. A source-scope instruction that clearly limits allowed source types must not remain only in shared_instruction. Product type values must be separated from shared_instruction: product_type_request_list owns requested product type phrases, and shared_instruction must not repeat those values.

For workflow_run_prompt_apply, priority_country_code must reflect the priority country requested in the workflow prompt as one ISO 3166 alpha-2 uppercase country code. The stage must not invent a default country when the workflow prompt does not choose one. The priority-country request must not remain duplicated in shared_instruction.

For workflow_run_prompt_apply, stage_instruction_list must preserve exact stage-specific instruction meaning from the workflow prompt and no longer duplicate those instructions in shared_instruction. Remove stage-specific instructions from shared_instruction is the required action-stage behavior; verification must fail when the result keeps one stage-specific instruction only in shared_instruction.
